            {
                "s2_paper_id": "1e8e97c0b39c149eafec8961249445f18a91f871",
                "title": "Research on scheduling strategy of virtual power plant based on multi-objective optimization of load-generating side",
                "year": 2023,
                "venue": "2023 IEEE 2nd International Conference on Electrical Engineering, Big Data and Algorithms (EEBDA)",
                "citation_count": 1,
                "reference_count": 11,
                "abstract": "Due to the strong volatility of renewable energy, there is a certain deviation between the actual output and the planned output. Therefore, two-way interaction between the generation side and the demand side is considered, which has important guiding significance for realizing the economic operation of virtual power plant. Therefore, the composition structure and operation mode of the virtual power plant are studied. By analyzing the effects of load side and generation side on the optimal scheduling of virtual power plant, an optimal scheduling model of virtual power plant based on multi-objective optimization of load - generation side was established. The results of example analysis fully prove that the optimized scheduling strategy of virtual power plant built in this paper can enhance the capacity of new energy consumption and reduce the operation cost of power grid.",
